In this statement, the President condemns and deplores the violence against peaceful citizens in Tunisia and praises the bravery and dignity of the Tunisian people. The United States expresses solidarity with the international community in supporting the Tunisian people's struggle for universal rights. The President urges all parties to remain calm and avoid violence, and calls on the Tunisian government to respect human rights and hold free and fair elections in the near future. The President emphasizes that each nation's democracy is unique, but those that respect the universal rights of their people are stronger and more successful. The President believes that Tunisia's future will be brighter if it is guided by the voices of its people.